<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-54-1271 </DOCNO><TEXT>Besides use as fuel gas, natural gas serves as raw material for the productionof chemical products like ammonia and methanol. It is used also for theproduction of gas mixtures which take part in chemical reactions or preventoxidation of products, etc. Direct oxidation of ores can be called achemical application of natural gas too. Possible natural gas applicationsare outlined. 7 figs., 5 refs.</TEXT></DOC>